verses.text_plain: The words of king Lemuel, the prophecy that his mother taught him.
verses.verse_html: 1The words of king Lemuel, the prophecy that his mother taught him.

verses.text_plain: What, my son? and what, the son of my womb? and what, the son of my vows?
verses.verse_html: 2What, my son? and what, the son of my womb? and what, the son of my vows?

verses.text_plain: Give not thy strength unto women, nor thy ways to that which destroyeth kings.
verses.verse_html: 3Give not thy strength unto women, nor thy ways to that which destroyeth kings.

verses.text_plain: It is not for kings, O Lemuel, it is not for kings to drink wine; nor for princes strong drink:
verses.verse_html: 4It is not for kings, O Lemuel, it is not for kings to drink wine; nor for princes strong drink:

verses.text_plain: Lest they drink, and forget the law, and pervert the judgment of any of the afflicted.
verses.verse_html:
5Lest they drink, and forget the law, and pervert the judgment of any of the afflicted. ▼
▼ pervert: Heb. alter
 , ▼
▼ of any…: Heb. of all the sons of affliction

footnotes.body_text: ▼ of any…: Heb. of all the sons of affliction
footnotes.body_html: ▼ of any…: Heb. of all the sons of affliction

verses.text_plain: Give strong drink unto him that is ready to perish, and wine unto those that be of heavy hearts.
verses.verse_html:
6Give strong drink unto him that is ready to perish, and wine unto those that be of heavy hearts. ▼
▼ of…: Heb. bitter of soul

tokens.text: unto him that is ready to perish
unto those that be of heavy

footnotes.body_html: ▼ of…: Heb. bitter of soul

verses.text_plain: Let him drink, and forget his poverty, and remember his misery no more.
verses.verse_html: 7Let him drink, and forget his poverty, and remember his misery no more.

verses.text_plain: Open thy mouth for the dumb in the cause of all such as are appointed to destruction.
verses.verse_html:
8Open thy mouth for the dumb in the cause of all such as are appointed to destruction. ▼
▼ such…: Heb. the sons of destruction

tokens.text: of all such as are appointed

footnotes.body_text: ▼ such…: Heb. the sons of destruction
footnotes.body_html: ▼ such…: Heb. the sons of destruction

verses.text_plain: Open thy mouth, judge righteously, and plead the cause of the poor and needy.
verses.verse_html: 9Open thy mouth, judge righteously, and plead the cause of the poor and needy.

verses.text_plain: Who can find a virtuous woman? for her price is far above rubies.
verses.verse_html: 10Who can find a virtuous woman? for her price is far above rubies.

verses.text_plain: The heart of her husband doth safely trust in her, so that he shall have no need of spoil.
verses.verse_html: 11The heart of her husband doth safely trust in her, so that he shall have no need of spoil.

tokens.text: in her, so that he shall have no need

verses.text_plain: She will do him good and not evil all the days of her life.
verses.verse_html: 12She will do him good and not evil all the days of her life.

verses.text_plain: She seeketh wool, and flax, and worketh willingly with her hands.
verses.verse_html: 13She seeketh wool, and flax, and worketh willingly with her hands.

verses.text_plain: She is like the merchants’ ships; she bringeth her food from afar.
verses.verse_html: 14She is like the merchants’ ships; she bringeth her food from afar.

verses.text_plain: She riseth also while it is yet night, and giveth meat to her household, and a portion to her maidens.
verses.verse_html: 15She riseth also while it is yet night, and giveth meat to her household, and a portion to her maidens.

tokens.text: also while it is yet night

verses.text_plain: She considereth a field, and buyeth it: with the fruit of her hands she planteth a vineyard.
verses.verse_html:
16She considereth a field, and buyeth it: with the fruit of her hands she planteth a vineyard. ▼
▼ buyeth: Heb. taketh

verses.text_plain: She girdeth her loins with strength, and strengtheneth her arms.
verses.verse_html: 17She girdeth her loins with strength, and strengtheneth her arms.

verses.text_plain: She perceiveth that her merchandise is good: her candle goeth not out by night.
verses.verse_html:
18She perceiveth that her merchandise is good: her candle goeth not out by night. ▼
▼ She…: Heb. She tasteth

footnotes.body_html: ▼ She…: Heb. She tasteth

verses.text_plain: She layeth her hands to the spindle, and her hands hold the distaff.
verses.verse_html: 19She layeth her hands to the spindle, and her hands hold the distaff.

verses.text_plain: She stretcheth out her hand to the poor; yea, she reacheth forth her hands to the needy.
verses.verse_html:
20She stretcheth out her hand to the poor; yea, she reacheth forth her hands to the needy. ▼
▼ She…: Heb. She spreadeth

footnotes.body_html: ▼ She…: Heb. She spreadeth

verses.text_plain: She is not afraid of the snow for her household: for all her household are clothed with scarlet.
verses.verse_html:
21She is not afraid of the snow for her household: for all her household are clothed with scarlet. ▼
▼ scarlet: or, double garments

footnotes.body_html: ▼ scarlet: or, double garments

verses.text_plain: She maketh herself coverings of tapestry; her clothing is silk and purple.
verses.verse_html: 22She maketh herself coverings of tapestry; her clothing is silk and purple.

verses.text_plain: Her husband is known in the gates, when he sitteth among the elders of the land.
verses.verse_html: 23Her husband is known in the gates, when he sitteth among the elders of the land.

verses.text_plain: She maketh fine linen, and selleth it; and delivereth girdles unto the merchant.
verses.verse_html: 24She maketh fine linen, and selleth it; and delivereth girdles unto the merchant.

verses.text_plain: Strength and honour are her clothing; and she shall rejoice in time to come.
verses.verse_html: 25Strength and honour are her clothing; and she shall rejoice in time to come.

verses.text_plain: She openeth her mouth with wisdom; and in her tongue is the law of kindness.
verses.verse_html: 26She openeth her mouth with wisdom; and in her tongue is the law of kindness.

verses.text_plain: She looketh well to the ways of her household, and eateth not the bread of idleness.
verses.verse_html: 27She looketh well to the ways of her household, and eateth not the bread of idleness.

verses.text_plain: Her children arise up, and call her blessed; her husband also, and he praiseth her.
verses.verse_html: 28Her children arise up, and call her blessed; her husband also, and he praiseth her.

verses.text_plain: Many daughters have done virtuously, but thou excellest them all.
verses.verse_html:
29Many daughters have done virtuously, but thou excellest them all. ▼
▼ have…: or, have gotten riches

footnotes.body_html: ▼ have…: or, have gotten riches

verses.text_plain: Favour is deceitful, and beauty is vain: but a woman that feareth the Lord, she shall be praised.
verses.verse_html: 30Favour is deceitful, and beauty is vain: but a woman that feareth the Lord, she shall be praised.

verses.text_plain: Give her of the fruit of her hands; and let her own works praise her in the gates.
verses.verse_html: 31Give her of the fruit of her hands; and let her own works praise her in the gates.
